result.name: Go San Ke Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text: When I entered the restaurant it was a nice atmosphere. I ordered the porkchop was it was dry, bland and a little thought furthermore, the sauce tasted strange (never tasted it in other restaurants before). Overall the place did everything else quite well.
Had a lunch there $150 total. Very good for a local place
Lunch with good variety of food , sushi platter at reasonable price$118

An impressively decent and cheap Japanese restaurant in an area not famously known for gourmet Japanese cuisine! Sashimi pieces were generously thick and fresh! Couple suggestions - try to use different brand of soy sauce as it tasted overly pungent and was in the sweet size; the texture of the rice used wasn’t quite like the ones I used to taste! Overall, a very satisfactory experience!
Fresh sashimi, quick service, very polite and attending staffs.
